Bankia, Mapfre: Iberian Equity Market Preview for July 20

-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 
2011-07-20T04:00:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/bankia-mapfre-iberian-equity-market-preview-for-july-20.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  Spain ’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  climbed 1 percent to 9,443.80 in
Madrid.  Portugal ’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  rose 1.6 percent to 6,664.80.  Spanish stocks:  Bankia SA (BKIA SM) starts trading in Madrid after raising
more than 3 billion euros ($4.2 billion) in an initial public
offering pricing shares at 3.75 euros each.  Mapfre SA (MAP)   said it has signed an agreement with
Euler Hermes SA to create a credit-insurance joint venture to
operate in Spain, Portugal and  Latin America . The joint venture
will have premiums of 200 million euros, based on 2010 figures,
the Spanish company said in a regulatory filing in Madrid. The
shares rose 1.7 percent to 2.40 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
